race.comment: ALL SAINTS (3) was ridden more conservatively at Kembla last time out over 1000m and she never really got into the race. Back to Country level now is a good move and she'll be better for the fresh run. Form last campaign stacks up and with the expectation that she'll get back to that level now, she looks the one to beat. BOSCO (1) led them up at the Sapphire Coast last start and just couldn't hold on, finishing 1.5L off the winner. The winkers go on now and he maps to be prominent from the outset once more. Fitter now and will be in this for a very long way. MRS FLANDERS (8) was trending the right way before a big defeat last start at Kembla. Back to country level now but her run two back was very impressive at Hawkesbury and she rates highly on that effort. Can play a leading role. REVEILLON (9) is not out of this on recent efforts. AIRFIELD (6) can play a role on resumption.
